These are the dot files I use on every UNIX system I have an account on,
though most of the time that is my MacBook, so some things may not work 100%
on Linux or other systems.

Preparing:

$ git clone git://github.com/bitserf/dotfiles.git bitserf-dotfiles
$ cd bitserf-dotfiles
$ git submodule update --init
$ cd .vim
$ git submodule update --init

Install files into $HOME. Will not clobber any existing files unless
you specify -f.

$ ./install.py 

